	affiliations = {University of Hyderabad, School of CIS, Hyderabad, TS, India},
	abstract = {Low-rank binary matrix approximation (LRBMA) is a special case of matrix approximation. LRBMA is, in general, a NP-Hard problem. Given a binary matrix A low-rank binary matrix approximation is to find a matrix A′ such that it’s rank is less than or equal to a given constant. Several algorithms exist in the literature to solve this problem. Some of these are exponential in time complexity. We try to achieve the similar results in polynomial time complexity. As an application to the proposed algorithm Autism Spectrum Disorder Detection problem is considered. Results show that the proposed algorithm is comparable to the existing algorithms that have exponential time complexity. © The Author(s), under exclusive licence to Springer Nature Singapore Pte Ltd. 2025.},
