	affiliations = {Northwest A&F University, School of Life Sciences, Yangling, Shaanxi, China; Nankai University School of Medicine, Tianjin, China},
	abstract = {Neurodevelopmental disorders (NDDs) present substantial challenges due to their intricate etiologies and varied clinical manifestations. Recent advancements in big data mining have revolutionized NDD research by facilitating the analysis of large, multifaceted datasets, thereby uncovering novel insights and therapeutic targets. This review provides a comprehensive overview of the recent progress in applying big data mining techniques to NDDs, highlighting key findings, methodological innovations, and future directions. We delve into advanced data mining techniques such as machine learning, statistical modeling, network analysis, and natural language processing, and their applications in identifying genetic variants, discovering biomarkers, elucidating molecular pathways, and improving diagnostic accuracy. Notable case studies include the identification of novel genetic variants through whole-genome sequencing, early ASD diagnosis using deep learning models on neuroimaging data, and the use of network analysis to reveal critical molecular pathways. Future directions involve developing more sophisticated AI and machine learning algorithms, exploring quantum computing for large-scale data analysis, and integrating novel data sources such as wearable devices and mobile health applications. Collaborative research and data-sharing initiatives are essential for overcoming current limitations and enhancing the potential of big data approaches. Ultimately, these efforts hold promise for significantly improving the lives of individuals affected by neurodevelopmental disorders through personalized medicine and precision therapeutics. © 2024 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
