	title = {Multi-Modal Health Monitoring for Autism and Anxiety},
	year = {2025},
	pages = {855 - 862},
	doi = {10.1109/ICESC65114.2025.11212372},
	url = {https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?eid=2-s2.0-105022601543&doi=10.1109%2FICESC65114.2025.11212372&partnerID=40&md5=93e5a7d65dff8ac4ef3dd476395e068f},
	affiliations = {Santhiram Engineering College, Department of Electrical & Computer Engineering, Kurnool, AP, India; Santhiram Engineering College, M-Tech Dept, Kurnool, AP, India; Rajeev Gandhi Memorial College of Engineering and Technology, Department of Electrical & Computer Engineering, Nandyal, AP, India; Ashoka Women's Engineering College, Kurnool, AP, India; SRM Institute of Science and Technology, Kattankulathur, TN, India},
	abstract = {Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD) and Anxiety Disorders (Generalized Anxiety Disorder [GAD] and Social Anxiety Disorder [SAD]) are common neurodevelopmental and neurological diseases with serious implications on the process of diagnosis and therapy. Routine monitoring and early diagnosis of these disorders can play an important role in the enhancement of quality of life and better recovery. This paper describes a multi-modal diagnostic and health monitoring device which aims at measuring and monitoring real time symptoms of autism and anxiety. The system combines the behavioral assessment, analysis of physiological conditions indicating, and the prediction assisted with AI to offer individual health assessment. Applications classified and diagonal monitored the severity of these disorders by training deep learning models (best_autism.pt), and ensemble machine learning pipelines (joblib models). Data on the systems can be put in dynamically through the score of a behavioral questionnaire and physiological data and the results will be risk assessments in real time. This mentioned platform has been developed with Streamlit and Python and can be used in both clinical and home environments and provides the possibility of early intervention via the help of digital health technologies. The results of this study show that they can use the system to obtain valid and real-time assessments, which will help identify ASD and anxiety disorders early and intervene. © 2025 IEEE.},
