	abstract = {Learning environments and instructional tools have a great impact on the learning process. For the children diagnosed with Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD) and other special conditions, social interaction and collaboration can be challenging in certain environments and situations, often leading to various difficulties in learning. Therefore, teachers and education policymakers need to design a more effective learning process to help these learners overcome these challenges. The study proposed the HoloDictionary, an application that embeds the holographic innovation as past findings have proven that holograms have positive impact on learning process as it promotes visual learning. This paper showcases a prototype developed using 3D modelling software for the production of holograms. The prototype was evaluated by a group of stakeholders in Mauritius and the findings revealed an optimistic result in employing such visual learning technology in educating the ASD learners. © 2025 IEEE.},
