	abstract = {Neuro-Developmental Disorders (NDDs), including Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD), Attention-Deficit/Hyperactivity Disorder( ADHD), and intellectual disabilities(ID), pose diagnostic and treatment challenges due to their diverse and overlapping characteristics. Artificial Intelligence(AI) and Machine Learning (ML) are important for the early detection, classification, and precise treatment of NDDs. This paper reviews advancements in predictive modeling, integrating various data types, and explainable AI. We assess initial diagnostic methodologies by examining neuroimaging, genetic, behavioral, and sociodemographic data, revealing that both traditional and deep learning approaches boost predictive accuracy. The study also considers practical, explainable, and resource-efficient strategies in environments with limited resources. This review highlights existing research directions and identifies gaps in clinical application and interpretability, setting the stage for improvements in AI-aided neurodevelopmental care. © 2025 IEEE.},
