	affiliations = {MNR, Beijing, China; Beihang University, Beijing, China; Ltd., Beijing, Beijing, China},
	abstract = {The GF-5 01A satellite is equipped with three payloads, including the AHSI (Airborne Hyperspectral Imaging) camera, enabling all-weather, multi-factor comprehensive detection capabilities for the atmosphere, water, and natural ecology. This paper evaluates the quality of surface reflectance from GF-5 01A AHSI data using three evaluation metrics: correlation coefficient, root mean square error, and spectral angle cosine. On one hand, it validates against ASD measured spectral data; on the other hand, it conducts cross-validation with hyperspectral data from different time phases. The results indicate that the surface reflectance spectrum of the GF-5 01A AHSI payload exhibits a certain level of stability, effectively identifying surface mineral information of chlorite. It demonstrates outstanding application capabilities in mineral information extraction in mining areas, geological environment monitoring of mines, and precise extraction of mineral information. © 2025 SPIE.},
