	abstract = {Recent virtual reality (VR) technology advances have provided innovative avenues for enhancing educational experiences, particularly in inclusive basic education. The research objective is to review the annual trend, word cloud, roles, application, and geographical contexts of VR technology integration in inclusive basic education. Using the PRISMA protocol, we analyzed data from Scopus and Google Scholar through a systematic literature review (SLR). The findings show that the annual publication of VR in inclusive basic education research has increased trend. The transformative roles of VR in inclusive basic education include inclusivity, virtual reality education, and visual education. There is significant consideration in the widespread application of VR in inclusive basic education settings such as VR for education, inclusive education, and autism education VR. Europe is the continent that has done the most research in this area. VR can potentially transform educational practices, making them more effective, inclusive, and engaging. © 2024 IEEE.},
