	affiliations = {MNR, Beijing, China; Beihang University, Beijing, China},
	abstract = {The ZY1-02E satellite can effectively acquire large-width multispectral, infrared, and hyperspectral data. The satellite is networked with the in-orbit ZY1-02D satellite, forming a globally leading operational Earth spectroscopy detection capability. It is capable of achieving full coverage of hyperspectral data across the entire land area of the country every six months, serving various industries such as disaster reduction, environmental protection, housing and transportation, agriculture, forestry, oceanography, and surveying. This paper evaluates the surface reflectance of ZY1-02E AHSI data using three evaluation metrics: correlation coefficient, root mean square error, and spectral angle cosine, and compares the results with ASD measured spectral data. The results indicate that the ZY1-02E AHSI payload can effectively identify information such as kaolinite and salinization, demonstrating outstanding application capabilities in mineral information extraction and salinization detection in mining areas. © 2024 IEEE.},
