	affiliations = {Jiangxi University of Chinese Medicine, Department of Psychosomatic Medicine, Nanchang, Jiangxi, China},
	abstract = {Purpose of the review: Traditional autism screening and diagnosis has some limitations, they cannot meet the needs of large-scale screening and diagnosis. The application of Artificial Intelligence (AI) technology to clinical medicine is a hot research topic recently, especially in mental health. China and international explorations of autism intelligent recognition technology have accumulated rich results in the fields of brain imaging, expression, eye movement and action, multimode, and classical task behaviour. Meanwhile, a variety of intelligent therapeutic robots based on modal interaction are also developed. This paper reviews the shortcomings of the traditional diagnostic techniques for autism and the current research status of AI in the diagnosis and treatment, hope to provide a reference for relevant research on Autism applications based on AI. Research methods: Literature on the application of AI in autism screening diagnosis and intervention in recent years was searched through literature navigation, and we analyse the aspects of autism screening, diagnosis and therapeutic intervention. Research conclusion: With the rapid development of artificial intelligence technology, it has become possible to use intelligent methods to carry out early large-scale senseless screening and diagnosis of Autism. In the future, research should focus on building an intelligent medical screening and diagnosis system for autism patient, developing screening tools and constructing an intelligent identification model for patients that integrates multimode data. © 2023 ACM.},
