	abstract = {ASD (Autism Spectrum Disorder) is behavioral and considered to be a developmental disorder found in human beings. It includes disorders in brain development, eventually affecting functional brain capabilities. It also affects how a person converses with others and causes problems in interaction and communication. The vast range of symptoms, abilities, and functioning levels in ASD patients is known as the "spectrum."It is essential to diagnose ASD at early stages so that autistic child can reach their full potential.In some cases, parents cannot accept that their child's mental growth is not developing along with physical development. With early diagnosis, children with autism can lead fulfilling and joyful lives through the provision of appropriate medication. Screening tests are used to diagnose this type of disorder but are time-consuming and costly. This research study has employed a convolutional neural network to detect the likelihood of ASD in young children at an early stage. Deep Neural Networks function well in many applications. This study has used Xception and Resnet50 model to predict ASD based on static facial images, especially in children. According to the results obtained, ResNet50's performance is better than Xception in Autism detection. © 2023 IEEE.},
