	affiliations = {Ajeenkya DY Patil University, School of Computer Science and Engineering, Pune, MH, India},
	abstract = {autism spectrum disorder (ASD) refers to a group of neurodevelopmental disorders that can result in motor and physical impairments. The majority of the time, children played alone rather than in groups. Autism spectrum disorders (ASDs) are a group of neurodevelopmental disorders that cause people to struggle with social interaction, age-appropriate play, and forming appropriate peer relationships for their developmental level. Nonetheless, most people will not work full-time or live alone. Although genetics and neurology have discovered intriguing risk patterns, no practical benefits have yet to be realized. There is still much work to be done to determine how and when behavioral and medical treatments are beneficial, as well as which children, particularly those with significant comorbidities, benefit from them. In this paper we proposed an autism application which will provide information about all the autosim disorder persons all over the India, rehabs, new centers for adults with autism spectrum disorders. We created an application using technologies like JAVA Script, SVG Map for maps, and HTML for web pages. In addition, we have included all autism-related information by state in this application, as well as a registration page for new centres, rehabs, associations, and non-governmental organizations (NGOs).Clinicians can assist families in navigating referrals and access to community support systems by providing timely and tailored assistance, providing accurate information in the face of sometimes unfiltered media input, and anticipating transitions such as family changes and school admission and exit. We chose this topic to contribute to healthcare innovation by raising awareness of undiagnosed syndromes. © 2023 IEEE.},
