	abstract = {Autism spectrum disorder (ASD) is a specific type of generalized developmental disorder characterized by social communication disorders and narrow, repetitive stereotypical behaviors. Augmented reality (AR) has gained considerable attention and research in the developmental intervention of autism with its combination of virtual and real characteristics. This paper systematically understands the characteristics of social disorders in autistic patients and the current effective intervention methods, and obtains the development enlightenment for effective intervention for autistic patients. Through the in-depth exploration of the definition and characteristics of augmented reality technology, the feature matching between augmented reality technology and autistic social communication disorder is analyzed in detail, and then the feasibility of application is obtained. Finally, based on the research examples of foreign augmented reality technology in the social disorders of autistic patients, the development enlightenment of future augmented reality technology in autistic patients with social disorders is summarized. © 2023 IEEE.},
